#. type: Title #
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Callback` - a wrapper around `callable`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This rule allows validation of the current property value (but not limited to it) with an arbitrary condition within a  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"callable. The benefit is that there is no need to create a separate custom "
"rule and handler."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "A condition can be within:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "Standalone callable function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "Callable class."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "DTO (data transfer object) method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"The downside of using standalone functions and DTO methods is a lack of "
"reusability. So they are mainly useful for some specific non-repetitive "
"conditions. Reusability can be achieved with callable classes, but depending "
"on other factors (the need for additional parameters for example), it might "
"be a good idea to create a full-fledged [custom rule](creating-custom-"
"rules.md) with a separate handler instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "The callback function signature is the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\ValidationContext;\n"
"\n"
"function (mixed $value, Callback $rule, ValidationContext $context): Result;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md guide/en/conditional-validation.md
msgid "where:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "`$value` is the validated value;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "`$rule` is a reference to the original `Callback` rule;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md guide/en/conditional-validation.md
msgid "`$context` is a validation context;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "returned value is a validation result instance with or without errors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using as a function"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"An example of passing a standalone callable function to a `Callback` rule:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\ValidationContext;\n"
"\n"
"new Callback(\n"
"    static function (mixed $value, Callback $rule, ValidationContext $context): Result {\n"
"        // The actual validation code.\n"
"        \n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    },\n"
");\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Value validation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"`Callback` rule can be used to add validation missing in built-in rules for "
"a single property's value. Below is the example verifying that a value is a "
"valid [YAML](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YAML) string (additionally "
"requires `yaml` PHP extension):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Exception;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"\n"
"new Callback(\n"
"    static function (mixed $value): Result {\n"
"        if (!is_string($value)) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError('The value must be a string.');\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        $notYamlMessage = 'This value is not a valid YAML.';\n"
"\n"
"        try {\n"
"            $data = yaml_parse($value);\n"
"        } catch (Exception $e) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        if ($data === false) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    },\n"
");\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> **Note:** Processing untrusted user input with `yaml_parse()` can be dangerous with certain settings. Please refer to\n"
"> [`yaml_parse()` docs](https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.yaml-parse.php) for more details. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Usage of validation context for validating multiple properties depending on each other"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"In the example below, the 3 angles are validated as degrees to form a valid "
"triangle:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Integer;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\ValidationContext;\n"
"\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    'angleA' => [\n"
"        new Required(),\n"
"        new Integer(),\n"
"    ],\n"
"    'angleB' => [\n"
"        new Required(),\n"
"        new Integer(),\n"
"    ],\n"
"    'angleC' => [\n"
"        new Required(),\n"
"        new Integer(),\n"
"    ],\n"
"\n"
"    new Callback(\n"
"        static function (mixed $value, Callback $rule, ValidationContext $context): Result {\n"
"            $angleA = $context->getDataSet()->getPropertyValue('angleA');\n"
"            $angleB = $context->getDataSet()->getPropertyValue('angleB');\n"
"            $angleC = $context->getDataSet()->getPropertyValue('angleC');\n"
"            $sum = $angleA + $angleB + $angleC;\n"
"            \n"
"            if ($sum <= 0) {\n"
"                return (new Result())->addError('The angles\\' sum can\\'t be negative.');\n"
"            } \n"
"            \n"
"            if ($sum > 180) {\n"
"                return (new Result())->addError('The angles\\' sum can\\'t be greater than 180 degrees.');\n"
"            }\n"
"            \n"
"            return new Result();\n"
"        }\n"
"    ),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Replacing boilerplate code with separate rules and `when`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"However, some cases of using validation context can lead to boilerplate code:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\ValidationContext;\n"
"\n"
"static function (mixed $value, Callback $rule, ValidationContext $context): Result {\n"
"    if ($context->getDataSet()->getPropertyValue('married') === false) {\n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    }\n"
"    \n"
"    $spouseAge = $context->getDataSet()->getPropertyValue('spouseAge');\n"
"    if ($spouseAge === null) {\n"
"        return (new Result())->addError('Spouse age is required.');\n"
"    }\n"
"    \n"
"    if (!is_int($spouseAge)) {\n"
"        return (new Result())->addError('Spouse age must be an integer.');\n"
"    }\n"
"    \n"
"    if ($spouseAge < 18 || $spouseAge > 100) {\n"
"        return (new Result())->addError('Spouse age must be between 18 and 100.');\n"
"    }        \n"
"    \n"
"    return new Result();\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"They can be rewritten using multiple rules and conditional validation making "
"code more intuitive. We can use built-in rules where possible:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\BooleanValue;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Integer;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\ValidationContext;\n"
"\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    'married' => new BooleanValue(),\n"
"    'spouseAge' => new Integer(\n"
"        min: 18,\n"
"        max: 100,\n"
"        when: static function (mixed $value, ValidationContext $context): bool {\n"
"            return $context->getDataSet()->getPropertyValue('married') === true;\n"
"        },\n"
"    ),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using as an object's method"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "For property"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"When using as a PHP attribute, set an object's method as a callback instead:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Exception;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"\n"
"final class Config {\n"
"    public function __construct(\n"
"        #[Callback(method: 'validateYaml')]\n"
"        private string $yaml,\n"
"    ) {\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    private function validateYaml(mixed $value): Result \n"
"    {\n"
"        if (!is_string($value)) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError('The value must be a string.');\n"
"        }\n"
"        \n"
"        $notYamlMessage = 'This value is not a valid YAML.';\n"
"\n"
"        try {\n"
"            $data = yaml_parse($value);\n"
"        } catch (Exception $e) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"        \n"
"        if ($data === false) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"The signature is the same as in a regular function. Note that there are no "
"restrictions on visibility levels and static modifiers, all of them can be "
"used (`public`, `protected`, `private`, `static`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"Using a `callback` argument instead of `method` with PHP attributes is "
"prohibited due to current PHP language restrictions (a callback can't be "
"inside a PHP attribute)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "For the whole object"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "It's also possible to check the whole object:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Exception;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"\n"
"#[Callback(method: 'validate')]\n"
"final class Config {\n"
"    public function __construct(        \n"
"        private int $yaml,\n"
"    ) {\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    private function validate(): Result \n"
"    {\n"
"        if (!is_string($this->yaml)) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError('The value must be a string.');\n"
"        }\n"
"        \n"
"        $notYamlMessage = 'This value is not a valid YAML.';\n"
"\n"
"        try {\n"
"            $data = yaml_parse($this->yaml);\n"
"        } catch (Exception $e) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"        \n"
"        if ($data === false) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Note the use of property value (`$this->yaml`) instead of method argument (`$value`).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using a callable class"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "A class that implements `__invoke()` can also be used as a callable:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Exception;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\ValidationContext;\n"
"\n"
"final class YamlCallback\n"
"{    \n"
"    public function __invoke(mixed $value): Result\n"
"    {\n"
"        if (!is_string($value)) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError('The value must be a string.');\n"
"        }\n"
"        \n"
"        $notYamlMessage = 'This value is not a valid YAML.';\n"
"\n"
"        try {\n"
"            $data = yaml_parse($value);\n"
"        } catch (Exception $e) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"        \n"
"        if ($data === false) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "The signature is the same as in a regular function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"Using in rules (note that a new instance must be passed, not a class name):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Callback;\n"
"\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    'yaml' => new Callback(new YamlCallback()),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shortcut for use with validator"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid ""
"When using with the validator and default `Callback` rule settings, a rule "
"declaration can be omitted, so just including a callable is enough. It will "
"be normalized automatically before validation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Exception;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Validator;\n"
"\n"
"$data = [];\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    'yaml' => static function (mixed $value): Result {\n"
"        if (!is_string($value)) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError('The value must be a string.');\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        $notYamlMessage = 'This value is not a valid YAML.';\n"
"\n"
"        try {\n"
"            $data = yaml_parse($value);\n"
"        } catch (Exception $e) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        if ($data === false) {\n"
"            return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"        }\n"
"\n"
"        return new Result();\n"
"    },\n"
"];\n"
"$result = (new Validator())->validate($data, $rules);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
msgid "Or it can be set within an array of other rules:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-callback.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Exception;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Result;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Validator;\n"
"\n"
"$data = [];\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    'yaml' => [\n"
"        new Required(),\n"
"        static function (mixed $value): Result {\n"
"            if (!is_string($value)) {\n"
"                return (new Result())->addError('The value must be a string.');\n"
"            }\n"
"        \n"
"            $notYamlMessage = 'This value is not a valid YAML.';\n"
"        \n"
"            try {\n"
"                $data = yaml_parse($value);\n"
"            } catch (Exception $e) {\n"
"                return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"            }\n"
"        \n"
"            if ($data === false) {\n"
"                return (new Result())->addError($notYamlMessage);\n"
"            }\n"
"        \n"
"            return new Result();\n"
"        },\n"
"    ],    \n"
"];\n"
"$result = (new Validator())->validate($data, $rules);\n"
msgstr ""
